                  <operation source="formula" to="temp.Tmp_Prompt_Request">
                     <expression language="XQuery">&lt;Generate_Content_Request&gt;
   &lt;contents&gt;
      &lt;parts&gt;
         &lt;text&gt;Given the following email subject and body, analyze the text and extract only one Zendesk ticket number in the exact format below: If the email contains a Zendesk ticket number, return: Zendesk Ticket Number: value If no Zendesk ticket number is found, return nothing. Rules: Only return one line, no extra text or explanation. The Zendesk ticket number is usually a numeric ID, often preceded by phrases like Zendesk ticket #12345 or ticket number 12345.
Email Text:
Subject: {$input.In_Email_Subject} 
Body: {$input.In_Email_Body} &lt;/text&gt;
      &lt;/parts&gt;
      &lt;role&gt;user&lt;/role&gt;
   &lt;/contents&gt;
 &lt;generationConfig&gt;
      &lt;stopSequences&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/stopSequences }&lt;/stopSequences&gt;
      &lt;candidateCount&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/candidateCount }&lt;/candidateCount&gt;
      &lt;maxOutputTokens&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/maxOutputTokens  }&lt;/maxOutputTokens&gt;
      &lt;temperature&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/temperature }&lt;/temperature&gt;
      &lt;topP&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/topP  }&lt;/topP&gt;
      &lt;topK&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration [1]/topK  }&lt;/topK&gt;
   &lt;/generationConfig&gt;
&lt;/Generate_Content_Request&gt;
</expression>
                  </operation>
